      <div class="msgContentFrame">I don't know if this &quot;bug&quot; or whatever it is, happen to many players, cause I didn't see a thread on it, but the &quot;bug&quot; is as followed. <br /> <br />I see an enemy. <br />I change into active mode. <br />I get in range to the enemy to execute my skills. <br />I hit my first skill to engage in battle(no matter what it is, it happened on any skill yet) <br />Now I don't perform the skill, instead it lags on the action and the next second my stamina bar is completely depleted, with the skill I wanted to use in queue. <br /> <br />This happens to me regularly. No matter if its an active or passive skill(Attack or Guard for example) <br />It doesn't really bother me too much, but it's just frustrating cause I need to wait for my stamina bar to refill again, so I can actually start the fight. <br /> <br />I also noticed this happens only when I just changed into active mode, not while I stay on active mode and start to fight another mob. <br /> <br />I have no clue what causes this bug, I tried to find any similiarities between the times it happens, but there is just none, except it only happens right after I changed to active mode and hit the first skill.</div>
